You have to update `background-size` to `cover` Update below css.

    .headerContainer {
        height: 100vh;
        border: solid 2px;
        background-image: url(https://i2.wp.com/oddshjelpen.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/350851-download-free-website-background-1920x1080-for-mobile-hd.jpg?ssl=1);
        background-size: cover;
        background-position: left-top;
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
    }

[Fiddle][1]


  [1]: https://jsfiddle.net/7s5g6eaj/1/

`contain` fills up one dimension (full width or full height) while `cover` fills the image up until both dimensions are touching the sides.

Also, don&#39;t have a fixed height value, because on smaller screens, your child elements will go outside the header. Replace `height` with `min-height`.


    .headerContainer{
      /* height:100vh; */
      min-height: 100vh;
      border:solid 2px;
      background-image:url(&quot;https://i2.wp.com/oddshjelpen.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/350851-download-free-website-background-1920x1080-for-mobile-hd.jpg?ssl=1&quot;);
      /* background-size: contain; */
      background-size: cover;
      background-position: left-top;
      background-repeat:no-repeat;
    }

